(598, 'BELLO', 'Hold him down, girls, till I squat on him. ', 'Hold him down, girls, till I squat on him. ', ''),
(599, 'ZOE', 'Yes. Walk on him! I will. ', 'Yes. Walk on him! I will. ', ''),
(600, 'FLORRY', 'I will. Don''t be greedy. ', 'I will. Don''t be greedy. ', ''),
(601, 'KITTY', 'No, me. Lend him to me. {The brothel cook, Mrs Keogh, wrinkled, greybearded, in a greasy bib, men''s grey and green socks and brogues, floursmeared, a rollingpin stuck with raw pastry in her bare red arm and hand, appears at the door.} ', 'No, me. Lend him to me.   ', '{The brothel cook, Mrs Keogh, wrinkled, greybearded, in a greasy bib, men''s grey and green socks and brogues, floursmeared, a rollingpin stuck with raw pastry in her bare red arm and hand, appears at the door.}'),
(602, 'MRS KEOGH', '{ferociously} Can I help? {They hold and pinion Bloom.} ', '  Can I help?   ', '{ferociously},{They hold and pinion Bloom.}'),
(603, 'BELLO', '{Squats with a grunt on Bloom''s upturned face, puffing cigarsmoke, nursing a fat leg} I see Keating Clay is elected vicechairman of the Richmond asylum and by the by Guinness''s preference shares are at sixteen three quaffers. Curse me for a fool that didn''t buy that lot Craig and Gardner told me about. Just my infernal luck, curse it. And that Goddamned outsider Throwaway at twenty to one. {he quenches his cigar angrily on Bloom''s ear} Where''s that Goddamned cursed ashtray? ', '  I see Keating Clay is elected vicechairman of the Richmond asylum and by the by Guinness''s preference shares are at sixteen three quaffers. Curse me for a fool that didn''t buy that lot Craig and Gardner told me about. Just my infernal luck, curse it. And that Goddamned outsider Throwaway at twenty to one.   Where''s that Goddamned cursed ashtray? ', '{Squats with a grunt on Bloom''s upturned face, puffing cigarsmoke, nursing a fat leg},{he quenches his cigar angrily on Bloom''s ear}'),
(604, 'BLOOM', '{goaded, buttocksmothered} O! O! Monsters! Cruel one! ', '  O! O! Monsters! Cruel one! ', '{goaded, buttocksmothered}'),
(605, 'BELLO', 'Ask for that every ten minutes. Beg. Pray for it as you never prayed before. {he thrusts out a figged fist and foul cigar} Here, kiss that. Both. Kiss. {he throws a leg astride and, pressing with horseman''s knees, calls in a hard voice} Gee up! A cockhorse to Banbury cross. I''ll ride him for the Eclipse stakes. {he bends sideways and squeezes his mount''s testicles roughly, shouting} Ho! Off we pop! I''ll nurse you in proper fashion. {he horserides cockhorse, leaping in the, in the saddle} The lady goes a pace a pace and the coachman goes a trot a trot and the gentleman goes a gallop a gallop a gallop a gallop. ', 'Ask for that every ten minutes. Beg. Pray for it as you never prayed before.   Here, kiss that. Both. Kiss.   Gee up! A cockhorse to Banbury cross. I''ll ride him for the Eclipse stakes.   Ho! Off we pop! I''ll nurse you in proper fashion.   The lady goes a pace a pace and the coachman goes a trot a trot and the gentleman goes a gallop a gallop a gallop a gallop. ', '{he thrusts out a figged fist and foul cigar},{he throws a leg astride and, pressing with horseman''s knees, calls in a hard voice},{he bends sideways and squeezes his mount''s testicles roughly, shouting},{he horserides cockhorse, leaping in the, in the saddle}'),
(606, 'FLORRY', '{pulls at Bello} Let me on him now. You had enough. I asked before you. ', '  Let me on him now. You had enough. I asked before you. ', '{pulls at Bello}'),
(607, 'ZOE', '{pulling at Florry} Me. Me. Are you not finished with him yet, suckeress? ', '  Me. Me. Are you not finished with him yet, suckeress? ', '{pulling at Florry}'),
(608, 'BLOOM', '{stifling} Can''t. ', '  Can''t. ', '{stifling}'),
(609, 'BELLO', 'Well, I''m not. Wait. {he holds in his breath} Curse it. Here. This bung''s about burst. {he uncorks himself behind: then, contorting his features, farts stoutly} Take that! {he recorks himself} Yes, by Jingo, sixteen three quarters. ', 'Well, I''m not. Wait.   Curse it. Here. This bung''s about burst.   Take that!   Yes, by Jingo, sixteen three quarters. ', '{he holds in his breath},{he uncorks himself behind: then, contorting his features, farts stoutly},{he recorks himself}'),
(610, 'BLOOM', '{a sweat breaking out over him} Not man. {he sniffs} Woman. ', '  Not man.   Woman. ', '{a sweat breaking out over him},{he sniffs}'),
(611, 'BELLO', '{stands up} No more blow hot and cold. What you longed for has come to pass. Henceforth you are unmanned and mine in earnest, a thing under the yoke. Now for your punishment frock. You will shed your male garments, you understand, Ruby Cohen? and don the shot silk luxuriously rustling over head and shoulders. And quickly too! ', '  No more blow hot and cold. What you longed for has come to pass. Henceforth you are unmanned and mine in earnest, a thing under the yoke. Now for your punishment frock. You will shed your male garments, you understand, Ruby Cohen? and don the shot silk luxuriously rustling over head and shoulders. And quickly too! ', '{stands up}'),
(612, 'BLOOM', '{shrinks} Silk, mistress said! O crinkly! scrapy! Must I tiptouch it with my nails? ', '  Silk, mistress said! O crinkly! scrapy! Must I tiptouch it with my nails? ', '{shrinks}'),
(613, 'BELLO', '{points to his whores} As they are now so will you be, wigged, singed, perfumesprayed, ricepowdered, with smoothshaven armpits. Tape measurements will be taken next your skin. You will be laced with cruel force into vicelike corsets of soft dove coutille with whalebone busk to the diamondtrimmed pelvis, the absolute outside edge, while your figure, plumper than when at large, will be restrained in nettight frocks, pretty two ounce petticoats and fringes and things stamped, of course, with my houseflag, creations of lovely lingerie for Alice and nice scent for Alice. Alice will feel the pullpull. Martha and Mary will be a little chilly at first in such delicate thighcasing but the frilly flimsiness of lace round your bare knees will remind you ..... ', '  As they are now so will you be, wigged, singed, perfumesprayed, ricepowdered, with smoothshaven armpits. Tape measurements will be taken next your skin. You will be laced with cruel force into vicelike corsets of soft dove coutille with whalebone busk to the diamondtrimmed pelvis, the absolute outside edge, while your figure, plumper than when at large, will be restrained in nettight frocks, pretty two ounce petticoats and fringes and things stamped, of course, with my houseflag, creations of lovely lingerie for Alice and nice scent for Alice. Alice will feel the pullpull. Martha and Mary will be a little chilly at first in such delicate thighcasing but the frilly flimsiness of lace round your bare knees will remind you ..... ', '{points to his whores}'),
(614, 'BLOOM', '{charming soubrette with dauby cheeks, mustard hair and large male hands and nose, leering mouth} I tried her things on only twice, a small prank, in Holles street. When we were hard up I washed them to save the laundry bill. My own shirts I turned. It was the purest thrift. ', '  I tried her things on only twice, a small prank, in Holles street. When we were hard up I washed them to save the laundry bill. My own shirts I turned. It was the purest thrift. ', '{charming soubrette with dauby cheeks, mustard hair and large male hands and nose, leering mouth}'),
(615, 'BELLO', '{jeers} Little jobs that make mother pleased, eh? And showed off coquettishly in your domino at the mirror behind closedrawn blinds your unskirted thighs and hegoat''s udders in various poses of surrender, eh? Ho! ho! I have to laugh! That secondhand black operatop shift and short trunkleg naughties all split up the stitches at her last rape that Mrs Miriam Dandrade sold you from the Shelbourne hotel, eh? ', '  Little jobs that make mother pleased, eh? And showed off coquettishly in your domino at the mirror behind closedrawn blinds your unskirted thighs and hegoat''s udders in various poses of surrender, eh? Ho! ho! I have to laugh! That secondhand black operatop shift and short trunkleg naughties all split up the stitches at her last rape that Mrs Miriam Dandrade sold you from the Shelbourne hotel, eh? ', '{jeers}'),
(616, 'BLOOM', 'Miriam. Black. Demimondaine. ', 'Miriam. Black. Demimondaine. ', ''),
(617, 'BELLO', '{guffaws} Christ Almighty it''s too tickling, this! You were a nicelooking Miriam when you clipped off your backgate hairs and lay swooning in the thing across the bed as Mrs Dandrade about to be violated by lieutenant Smythe-Smythe, Mr Philip Augustus Blockwell M. P., signor Laci Daremo, the robust tenor, blueeyed Bert, the liftboy, Henri Fleury of Gordon Bennett fame, Sheridan, the quadroon Croesus, the varsity wetbob eight from old Trinity, Ponto, her splendid Newfoundland and Bobs, dowager duchess of Manorhamilton. {he guffaws again} Christ, wouldn''t it make a Siamese cat laugh? ', '  Christ Almighty it''s too tickling, this! You were a nicelooking Miriam when you clipped off your backgate hairs and lay swooning in the thing across the bed as Mrs Dandrade about to be violated by lieutenant Smythe-Smythe, Mr Philip Augustus Blockwell M. P., signor Laci Daremo, the robust tenor, blueeyed Bert, the liftboy, Henri Fleury of Gordon Bennett fame, Sheridan, the quadroon Croesus, the varsity wetbob eight from old Trinity, Ponto, her splendid Newfoundland and Bobs, dowager duchess of Manorhamilton.   Christ, wouldn''t it make a Siamese cat laugh? ', '{guffaws},{he guffaws again}'),
(618, 'BLOOM', '{her hands and features working} It was Gerald converted me to be a true corsetlover when I was female impersonator in the High School play Vice Versa. It was dear Gerald. He got that kink, fascinated by sister''s stays. Now dearest Gerald uses pinky greasepaint and gilds his eyelids. Cult of the beautiful. ', '  It was Gerald converted me to be a true corsetlover when I was female impersonator in the High School play Vice Versa. It was dear Gerald. He got that kink, fascinated by sister''s stays. Now dearest Gerald uses pinky greasepaint and gilds his eyelids. Cult of the beautiful. ', '{her hands and features working}'),
(619, 'BELLO', '{with wicked glee} Beautiful! Give us a breather! When you took your seat with womanish care, lifting your billowy flounces, on the smoothworn throne. ', '  Beautiful! Give us a breather! When you took your seat with womanish care, lifting your billowy flounces, on the smoothworn throne. ', '{with wicked glee}'),
(620, 'BLOOM', 'Science. To compare the various joys we each enjoy. {earnestly} And really it''s better the position .... because often I used to wet .... ', 'Science. To compare the various joys we each enjoy.   And really it''s better the position .... because often I used to wet .... ', '{earnestly}');
